thorization2star  aThis collection of articles takes a long look at the dynamics of regionalism in Eastern Asia and shows how although the past limits the future, its hold on our possibilities for peaceful coexistence is not as strong as we think. What makes this volume unique is that Taiwanese scholars are brought together with Malaysian scholars to discuss a subject that is vital to the future of both East and Southeast Asians. Japan's diplomatic history as well as the heritage of its conquest of Eastern Asia is examined alongside China's cultural geography, paradigmatic dynamics, and intra-regional economics. Ties between East Asia and Southeast Asia, as well as the influence of American military power and European integration are also thoroughly dealt with. The end result is that the reader is offered multidisciplinary perspectives on present and future regional trends.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aRegionalismzEast AsiaxCongresses. 0aRegionalismzSoutheast AsiaxCongresses. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Globalization.2bisacsh1 aBakar, Mohamad Abu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeng, Ooi Kee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChieh-Lin, Hsu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChoo Ming, Ding, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGanesan, N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHsu, Klaus C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKee Beng, Ooi, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKim, Khoo Kay, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMing, Ding Choo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNarayanan, Arujunan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.